-- U.S. Stocks Trim Losses After ECB Says It Will Help Cyprus
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2013-03-19T19:17:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-19/u-s-stocks-trim-losses-after-ecb-says-it-will-help-cyprus.html
U.S. stocks trimmed losses after
the European Central Bank said it will provide liquidity to
Cyprus after the nation’s Parliament rejected a tax on bank
deposits needed to win a financial bailout.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index was down 0.2 percent at
1,548.32 at 3:16 p.m. in New York after falling as much as 0.9
percent earlier. The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  climbed 6.45
points to 14,458.51 after tumbling almost 70 points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael P. Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  